        <h2>Leave Management System</h2>

        <div class="section">
            <h3>Overview</h3>
            <p>The Leave Management System is a web-based application built using ASP.NET Core Razor Pages, aimed at businesses and organizations to efficiently manage employee leave. The application provides a simple, user-friendly interface for employees to request leave, while enabling administrators and managers to review, approve, or reject requests.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h3>Features</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Employee Dashboard:</strong> Employees can log in and view their leave balance, past leave records, and submit new leave requests.</li>
                <li><strong>Leave Request:</strong> Employees can easily submit leave requests with options for selecting leave type (e.g., sick leave, annual leave, personal leave), start and end dates, and adding remarks or attachments.</li>
                <li><strong>Leave Types:</strong> Supports different leave types like paid leave, sick leave, maternity/paternity leave, and others, configurable by administrators.</li>
                <li><strong>Leave Balances:</strong> Tracks the leave balances of employees and allows administrators to set or update leave quotas.</li>
                <li><strong>Approval Workflow:</strong> Managers and administrators can review submitted leave requests and approve or reject them with comments.</li>
                <li><strong>Notifications:</strong> Automated notifications and email alerts for employees and managers regarding leave status, reminders, and updates.</li>
                <li><strong>Reports and Analytics:</strong> Provides reporting and analytics on leave trends, leave utilization, and employee productivity.</li>
                <li><strong>Admin Portal:</strong> Administrators can manage leave settings, manage users, and customize leave policies through a dedicated admin interface.</li>
                <li><strong>Security & Authentication:</strong> Secure login using roles-based access control (RBAC) with authentication via Azure Active Directory or custom user management.</li>
                <li><strong>Mobile Responsiveness:</strong> Ensures a responsive design for both desktop and mobile devices, providing seamless leave management experience.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
